pull_request.title: Add CompletableFuture Support for Callback-based Async RPC
pull_request.body:
### Motivation:

[Issue #945](https://github.com/sofastack/sofa-rpc/issues/945)
SOFA-rpc uses a callback-based asynchronous response model and lacks the ability to to handle async responses with
CompletableFuture introduced in Java8. Developers need to manually wrap the callback to integrate with chain operations,
which is inconvenient.
[Pull #1323](https://github.com/sofastack/sofa-rpc/pull/1323)
The issue had been addressed before. But letting ResponseFuture inherit CompletionStage is too intrusive and could introduce compatibility issues across the codebase.

### Modification:

- Introduces new bridge class SofaCallbackCompletableFuture
  - Integrates with RpcInvokeContext 
  - Compatible with callback mechanism with support of chain operations
- Integration test with real RPC

### Result:

- Avoided modifications to ResponseFuture
- Can now use CompletableFuture API directly in callbacks

## Usage Example
```java
// Create future instance first
SofaCompletableResponseFuture<String> future = SofaCompletableResponseFuture.create();

// Make RPC call
service.sayHello("test", 22);

// Chain process
String result = future
    .thenApply(res -> res + " (process1)")
    .thenApply(res -> res + " (process2)")
    .get(5, TimeUnit.SECONDS);
```

This is my first PR . I'm happy to make any changes as needed—thanks!

<!-- This is an auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->

## Summary by CodeRabbit

- **New Features**
  - Introduced a new asynchronous future class for enhanced non-blocking RPC response handling.
- **Tests**
  - Added comprehensive integration tests to validate asynchronous service calls, exception propagation, timeouts, cancellations, and callback chaining.

<!-- end of auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->
